{"bgColorIndex":0,"textColorIndex":0,"note":"# The task is to create a NumPy array with consecutive numbers from a start to an end number (inclusive).\n# Here's how to write that in a Jupyter Notebook using NumPy.\n\nimport numpy as np\n\n# Function to create and print a consecutive array from start to end number (inclusive)\ndef create_and_print_consecutive_array(start, end):\n    # Use NumPy's arange to create an array from start to end+1 (since end is inclusive)\n    consecutive_array = np.arange(start, end+1)\n    # Print the consecutive array\n    return consecutive_array\n\n# Example usage for start=2 and end=5\n# In a Jupyter Notebook, you would replace these with user input\nstart_example = 2\nend_example = 5\n\n# Call the function and print the output\ncreate_and_print_consecutive_array(start_example, end_example)\n\n——————\n\nimport numpy as np\n\ndef create_and_print_consecutive_array(start, end):\n    consecutive_array = np.arange(start, end+1)\n    return consecutive_array\n\nstart_example = 2\nend_example = 5\ncreate_and_print_consecutive_array(start_example, end_example)\n"}